item.description: Deep Learning Studies for Handwritten Digit Classification Overview PyTorch, TensorFlow, and Keras are the three selected open-source software for building an elementary convolutional neural network(CNN). PyTorch is an open source machine learning library written in Python, used for applications like natural language processing. TensorFlow is an open-source software and symbolic math library for dataflow programming across various tasks, used for applications like neural networks. Keras is a high level API also written in python to manage different libraries, which focuses on being modular, extensible, and user-friendly.
